Former minister of aviation, Femi Fani-Kayode, FFK, has reacted to the death of a beauty queen who died as a result of buttocks enlargement surgery performed on her.The beauty queen who is the 2013 Face of Democracy Transformation, Onwuzuligbo Nneka Miriam, died on February 3rd after a 31days coma from December 30th when the surgical operation was done on her by an American uncertified Surgeon Dr. Anu.Reacting to the death of the beauty queen, Just heard about the ex-beauty queen who died during a buttock enlargement procedure in Lagos. So Sad. And what a terrible way to go. The surgeon that did the operation is now on the run. Those that are not satisfied with their buttocks must beware. Vanity upon vanity! RIP.